                "titre": "Storyteller Sit-downs: Jillian Eugenios10.",
                "information": "<h3 name='cde5' id='cde5' class='graf graf--h3 graf-after--figure'><strong class='markup--strong markup--h3-strong'>What’s the difference between covering the news and working at Great Big&nbsp;Story?</strong></h3>\n<p name='b742' id='b742' class='graf graf--p graf-after--h3'>JE: As a reporter, I felt like I failed if I wrote a story and my sources liked what I’d written. You don’t want to surprise people, or burn bridges, but you don’t necessarily want to please the people you write about — your job, at its best, is to be challenging and critical while informing your readers. I took that very seriously.</p>\n<p name='1210' id='1210' class='graf graf--p graf-after--p'>My work at Great Big Story is different, and special in its own way.</p>\n<p name='0216' id='0216' class='graf graf--p graf-after--p'>We are being let into people’s lives — quite often, we sit with them in their homes — and they trust us. I’m not out to “get” anyone anymore. The goal is to let you, our viewer, into someone’s life and experience what it’s like to be them. We’re just the middlemen trying to get it right.</p>10.",
