                                    "libelle": "<p class='qtext_para'>I'm trying to make a psychological profile of the person who could ask these type of questions, I mean, I'm amazed that how seriously you think about life. This question seems so ironical.</p><p class='qtext_para'>Believe me, if that chicken which you had in your lunch today could eat you as you did, it would had done it in a blink of an eye.</p><p class='qtext_para'>A chicken’s life may not be important for us, or for that instance any other entity on Earth but for them it does, same as we value our lives.</p><p class='qtext_para'>The point of living your present life is noway related to any afterlife, even if it exists. Who cares?</p><p class='qtext_para'>Your present life's value can better be inculcated by a human who's on the bed of death, pleading some seconds more to live.</p><ul><li>Its the connections which you have in your present life, makes you want to live.</li><li>It's the expectations which gives you a strong reason to live.</li><li>It's the desires which makes you greedy to live.</li><li>It's the love which makes you stay.</li><li>It's that every second which you had lived, no matter of sorrow or happiness, of grief or joy, it counts. You want it, no matter how much you deny, you do.</li></ul><p class='qtext_para'>Even if there's no God or no afterlife, there's so much more here on Earth, till you're alive. Why don't make the best of it and cherish the memories in future.</p>",
