                                    "id": 4,
                                    "libelle": "<p class='qtext_para'>Why does a lion consider its life more important than a gazelle's?</p><p class='qtext_para'>Why does the gazelle consider its life more important than the lion's?</p><p class='qtext_para'>Who cares?</p><p class='qtext_para'>Look, you wrote this question in English and it has a religious sub-text so I will safely assume you are an American.</p><p class='qtext_para'>As such, you are not trapped in your situation. Hard work, limited and thrifty spending, and a goal can improve your life greatly, often in less than a year.</p><p class='qtext_para'>Understand there doesn't HAVE to be a point in life. You came into it not caring if there was, when did that change for you?</p><p class='qtext_para'>I'm guessing about when you found religion…or when religion found you if your family started you at it early.</p><p class='qtext_para'>Look, the world in all its beauty and splendor is out there to be seen. You are here for only a finite amount of time so if you see no point in your unenjoyable life then I see you have only a handful of choices:</p><ol><li>Keep living your unenjoyable life and complain about it forever.</li><li>End it all.</li><li>Make a plan, stick to your plan and start living an enjoyable life.</li></ol><p class='qtext_para'>It's your life after all. Not anyone else's. Their expectations are only that. You have control of your own life.</p><p class='qtext_para'>So act like it.</p>",
