                                    "id": 5,
                                    "libelle": "<p class='qtext_para'>If there is no afterlife and after death your consciousness ceases to exist then what is the purpose of life?</p></blockquote><p class='qtext_para'>Let me start off with an example.</p><p class='qtext_para'>Lets Assume that you’ve bought a brand new Apple iPhone Just now.</p><p class='qtext_para'>You un-boxed, turned it on, created a new apple ID, started downloading apps from appstore, begin making calls, messages and use apps.</p><p class='qtext_para'>Things go on. After many many months, And one fine yet a bad day you got too unfortunate to drop your phone into a bonfire and its considered completely useless and declared fully unusable and dead.</p><p class='qtext_para'>We all now know, not even its parts be used for refurbishing after such an incident/accident.</p><p class='qtext_para'>Now, we clearly know that this iPhone although of living its glorious life has came to an end and there is no afterlife to it of any sought, and its physical presence has completely ceased to exist from its own glorious shiny form and it is now just broken down to ashes.</p><p class='qtext_para'>Now, tell me what was the purpose of that iPhone you bought ? and why did you even buy it at the first place ?</p><blockquote><p class='qtext_para'>If you do not enjoy life then wouldn’t it be literally better if you killed yourself?</p></blockquote><p class='qtext_para'>That’s completely up to the individual. “enjoyment of life” is a private opinion that belongs solely to each and every individual. And, killing oneself too is. There are laws to punish suicide attempts but it matters only if they catch you alive before you succeed. (“ironic”)</p><blockquote><p class='qtext_para'>If humans are not special then why is human life considered more precious than a chicken’s life?</p></blockquote><p class='qtext_para'>A human life is so very special and its considered most precious by ‘Humans’ not by the chicken nor their cousins Ducks or Turkeys. Its our sole arrogance to feel we are on top of the food chain and we are great. Humans seldom understand that they are the part of a bigger ecosystem, they just ‘want’ to feel superior and to believe blindly that they are on top of it and may be since it was boring on the top for them, they then created something called God and placed it above them to criticize and blame for their mistakes and/or misunderstandings. [Must say, poor guy, this God is]</p><p class='qtext_para'>If the purpose of this question is to find the answer to ‘purpose of life’, then my answer would be to “live it the way you like it”.</p><p class='qtext_para'>But there is a catch, don’t make your life at the expense of another life.</p>",
